post_text:
Week 1 is over. Now for Week 2. It is so good to see the staff and students on campus. Thanks to everyone for your support. We are all learning.

We are blessed not to have a Covid 19 case on campus yet! Keep up the great job of wearing mask while social distancing and washing your hands! The excellent staff is cleaning, planning remote lessons, and educating in person. It takes a lot of teamwork. Thank you for being in our tribe!

Remember to check for temperatures and other Covid 19 symptoms each morning before arrival. Please stay home if you are sick or have had close contact with a lab-confirmed Covid 19 case. We need to be vigilant at keeping Covid 19 off of campus!

Please call or email if you need any information.

Remember, visitors are limited. Call ahead for an appointment.You must screen before entry. No student lunches may be delivered at this time. Students need to bring water or water bottles.

Thanks again for all the positive attitudes!

post_text: Avinger boy athletes. We will begin our summer workouts on Monday 6/15 at 3 PM. When you arrive please remain in your vehicle and follow social distancing protocols until asked by a member of the coaching staff to enter the gym.These workouts are ONLY open to current Avinger students due to the risk of Covid-19. All equipment used will be disinfected prior to, during, and after your departure but maintain a proper distance at all times to ensure your safety, as well of that of your teammates. There will be no live drills or scrimmaging of any kind on the school‚Äôs grounds.
